======================
Assignment operations:
======================
valid:
------
float=float
bool=bool
int=int
invalid:
--------
otherwise, value is not assigned and remains null
identifier is considered uninitialized

======================
Arithmetic operations:
======================
Valid:
------
int   =  int   (+,-,*,/) int 
float =  float (+,-,*,/) float
float =  int   (+,-,*,/) float
float =  float (+,-,*,/) int
--------
invalid:
--------
types - Error: Mismatch
int   (+,-,*,/) bool => type = unknown, value = value(int)
float (+,-,*,/) bool => type = unknown, value = value(float)
Division by zero -> value is zero
--------------------------
undeclared, uninitialized:
Error: Both must have a numberical value
unknown type
===========
Comparisons:
============
valid:
------
int (>,<,<=,>=) int
float (>,<,<=,>=) float
invalid:
-------
undeclared, uninitialized, invalid types-> unknown type






